# Query & Performance Rules

- Avoid duplicate queries across load functions and components.
- Keep server load functions efficient and cache-aware where appropriate.
- Paginate large result sets.
- Use indexes for columns used in `eq`, `in`, sorting, and foreign-key joins.
- Call out N+1 query risks.
- Avoid client-side overfetching.
- Prefer optimistic UI only when failure handling is clear and safe.
- Do not introduce polling where realtime subscriptions or explicit refresh would be better.
- Use Supabase realtime only when the feature truly needs it.
